nt manner while minimizing interruption to on-going processes. Responsible for the monitoring and recovery procedures of mission-critical enterprise systems. The System Administrator is responsible to maintain high availability, redundancy, and load balancing to the application to fulfill our expectation of incredibly high uptime. This position takes direction from the Senior Director, IT. Duties and Responsibilities Manage the day-to-day operations of the host computers by monitoring system performance, configuration, maintenance, and repair. Applies revisions to host system firmware and works with vendors to assist support activities. Ensure high availability and acceptable levels of performance of mission-critical host computer resources. Ensure that records of system downtime and equipment inventory are properly maintained to provide the management team with statistics for SLA monitoring and compliance. Analyze system logs to identify potential issues with computer systems. Perform routine audits of systems and software; performing backups as required. Collect and review system data to assist in capacity and planning purposes. Implement new system and application implementation plans, custom scripts and testing procedures to ensure operational reliability. Train technical staff in how to use new software and hardware. Perform the troubleshooting as required; lead problem-solving efforts often involving outside vendors and other support personnel and/or organizations. Establish, maintain and assist in managing Linux, MS Server, and VMware systems. Install, modify and maintain systems and utility software on server computer systems. Provide server support related to other application software. Follow guidelines and methods for the installation and management of the host computer operating systems, disk arrays, switches, and other components. Implement procedures to maintain security and protect systems from unauthorized use, acts of nature and user abuse. Develop procedures, programs, and documentation for support, maintenance, backup and restoration of host operating systems and host-based applications. Follow project directions and schedules to maximize benefits and minimize impacts on customer organizations. Develop tools, procedures, and training sessions for staff. Document system maintenance and repair in appropriate systems. Manage, along with others, the data center and computer host systems including hardware, software, and associated support systems. Stay current with technological developments in systems administration technology and recommend ways to take advantage of new technology. Support and adhere to company Change Management procedures. Perform technology needs analysis. Qualifications and Experience Requirements Required Bachelor's degree in a technical field such as Computer Information Systems, Management Information Systems, Computer Science, or Computer Engineering, etc. MCSE or MCSA. Minimum 6 years of professional hands-on experience supporting application and server technologies in a heterogeneous environment containing Linux and Microsoft servers. Hands-on experience supporting application/server: 6 years. Experience with Windows, Linux, VMware servers, and security: 2 years. Knowledge of database (SQL Server) and web server technology. Familiar with monitoring and metrics tools. Be available on call to provide support services during off-hours. Scheduled night and weekend work are required. The ability to travel as needed. Ability to communicate effectively. Preferred Certifications in Linux, Microsoft, or server/database technologies. Experience with VOIP components and converged networks. Healthcare experience. Experience with Sarbanes-Oxley and HIPAA requirements. ",
